  "original_title": "\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0da7\u0db4\u0dd4 \u0da2\u0db1\u0dcf\u0db0\u0dd2\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0d9c\u0ddd\u0da8\u0dcf\u0db7\u0dba\u0da7 \u0d85\u0d9c\u0db8\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0db4\u0dd4\u0dc5\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Former President Gotabaya can become Prime Minister",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Parliamentarian Major Pradeep Udugoda said today (25) that he has no reluctance to appoint former President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa to the post of Prime Minister and would express his consent if such a proposal is presented.",
        "Mr. Pradeep Udugoda said that there is no obstacle for Gotabhaya Rajapaksa to come to the country as he was a president who won 69 lakh votes and was an officer who led the war to victory.",
        "Mr. Udugoda further said that the Human Rights Commission has also confirmed the right of Mr. Gotabhaya Rajapaksa to return to Sri Lanka and that he cannot make statements about the political decisions of the former president.",
        "Parliamentarian Major Pradeep Udugoda said at the press conference held today (25) at the Sri Lanka Lanka Podujana Peramuna party office at Battaramulla Nelum Mawatha.",
        "Colombo District Member of Parliament Mr. Madhura Vithanage, who participated in the press conference, said that there is no obstacle for former President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa to come to Sri Lanka."
      ],
